Caption: The Georgia Tech EcoCommons is an 8-acre revitalized greenspace designed and engineered to reduce stormwater runoff while also supporting increased biodiversity and living-learning laboratories on campus. Siphoning runoff into cisterns, the system prevents millions of gallons of stormwater from entering the city‚Äôs sewer system. üíõüåé #EarthDay #WeCanDoThat
